      "text": [
        " «سُبْحَانَ اَللَّهِ وَ أَنْتُمْ مُحْرِمُونَ» قَالُوا إِنَّمَا هُوَ مِنَ اَلْبَحْرِ قَالَ «فَارْمُسُوهُ فِي اَلْمَاءِ إِذَنْ»."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2732 - Abu Ja'far (as) passed by a group of people eating locusts and said: \"Glory be to Allah (swt)! And you are in the state of ihram?\"\nThey said, \"It is from the sea.\"\nImam (as) replied: \"Then return it to the water.\""
        ]
      }
    },
